  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promotion of the MAB Programme and communication strategy</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Lima Action Plan endorsed by the 4th World Congress of Biosphere Reserves and adopted by the 28th session of the MAB Council on 19 March 2016 gave responsibility to the MAB Secretariat (D2.1; D2.2; D2.3; D2.4) to create a global communication strategy and action plan alongside with national and subnational authorities, MAB national committees (D2.1; D2.2) and regional networks (D2.2). Since the adoption of the Lima Action Plan, and as recommended by the MAB Council the Secretariat organized several regional meetings, including a kick-off meeting with members of the Advisory Committee and of the MAB Secretariat and regional workshops to co-design a global communication strategy.</narrative>
  </description>
